The paper discusses the integration of mobile edge computing (MEC) with 5G and beyond technologies, which primarily fall under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) and wireless power transfer and energy harvesting, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and augmented reality (AR), which are related to computer graphics (cs.AR) and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI, followed by cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.AR, and cs.SY.
